Teen dies after failing to stop for police
A TEENAGER who failed to stop for police was killed 10 minutes later when his car hit a tree in Brisbane's northwest.
POLICE had attempted to intercept the 17-year-old's vehicle on Samford Road, Keperra, about 12.30am Saturday.

When the vehicle failed to stop, officers pulled to the side of the road, police said. The teen kept driving and struck a tree on Settlement Road about 12.40am. He was pronounced dead at the scene. The Forensic Crash Unit is investigating and the Ethical Standards Command have been advised, police said.
